{"type":"message","id":"089db5a6","parentId":"b68def93","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:39:49.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Refining the report script**\n\nI need to inspect the generated markdown to see if it's sufficient. I notice there's a rolling summary with five selected positives and two negatives, but there are too many windows with no samples. With a majority threshold of eight, it shows zero sample windows and may need adjusting. This sparse sample issue could be useful to note in the initial report. Enhancing the script to calculate selected sampled windows and their positive ratio might be a good idea. I'll consider these improvements before the final commit since the user wants continuity.\n\n**Improving script and report**\n\nI want to improve the script and report to accurately reflect sparse samples and avoid misleading results. I'll add fields for counting sampled windows with non-null edges and validating the majority sample against the baseline. The out-of-sample pass criteria could benefit from ensuring a majority of sampled windows are valid. I notice Candidate A has a positive validation, while Candidate B is preferred for training despite a negative validation, indicating possible overfitting. I’ll update the markdown to include these insights before generating the final user-facing response.\n\n**Updating script and reports**\n\nI need to commit the script and outputs, marking the active task as done. It might be a good idea to simplify the report path names to something like \"date_tag 20260327_rule2_oos.\" I should carefully edit the script to include the summary and ensure the conclusion logic remains intact. I'll inspect the relevant snippets to make precise edits, using a search for line references. It seems I'll also need to read partial sections while building the selected summary and conclusion.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0a18d76e314b89270169c65e683204819885f3d506a0c1295d\",\"type\"