{"type":"message","id":"7bbe705f","parentId":"2e9405dd","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:05:16.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Creating a shadow candidates log**\n\nI’m thinking about generating a daily shadow candidates log from the current data and perhaps producing an initial snapshot report of the history. It might be easier to create a ledger generation script for historical backfill to simulate a shadow run and generate a ledger of hits. I need to make sure I have the right detail file and panel to produce a CSV with specified columns. It feels feasible to implement the script and create a new ACTIVE_TASK. Let’s see how to proceed.\n\n**Deciding on task commitment**\n\nI’m considering whether or not to commit the changes, since internal tasks may require a commitment after edits. I could definitely do a commit, but first, I need to inspect the existing detail columns. From earlier, I need to check for ai_decision, trend_prediction, price_action_state_code, and future_return_pct. I’ll create a simple script that reads the same detail and panel, computes fast_pct60, and generates rows for both the main and reference candidates. Using the same-day baseline average sounds good too!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0a18d76e314b89270169c6725a81a481988f826716e8e14f73\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpxnJtjqMxcf8kuM2XDfA9BXNg8JIyDHuAPtXNxkOZQDuqUqlJLe2Bfp7ozSG6TnRK1gqYGouGFDk27J_FffJSv8TpUEXiAybpugJQhBo21FBQzkxCPnoCLduNljp1JQMW7g4tWDTPQyFG2iQCW8zWfi9ChFPCqNnhHA7ol85M06uEiWMjkPFEYEgtNbbG79O0emFfo5QSKwsOuYuu8O3VzG_PpZ9ySv_SBXGUn9UrI8bBvBbiiFhKGe3X7geUw3UqmBunrXQezfLOcKxerRXT4MO4ShjQiSNlnp7PYKvrg6J1uMI-QAx6tDW5GLnN4GPh17fcoYSjxrIuJMA4PHhEpWUCYeA5ajTD3wok10hsO6TE4eqHOVaWA6xQFWWH_Cd8sxL81LnsyRW5Rb6PGrnPZevM6pbnV3smQGnXPvE_pcGr_9dZzZsZGc2OLQwTFpINie5v3nQeio3SyMbY4twEz16SoqMSqlJ_abYvnH4N9ZFnYaMFo0i0yvNewkigZGjUWXiX0ciM4mvJuep5yUws21nwz2O7HqlWxiTdCN-qARJgdEcQj3HP6BKkrtsQoHJreUz8WSOwkA_xH1hB82JJyKwn9MdWZxS71eTC